    <title>url/remotelink <lnpid>id-ST09-32635</lnpid></title>
    <body>

            <p>Use case <sourcexml>url/remotelink</sourcexml>: when the content of <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml> does not begin with <b>"http"</b> or <b>"www."</b> but the content of <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml> seems like a url and <sourcexml>remotelink/@hrefclass</sourcexml> is having value <b>http</b> then conversion should follow below instruction:.</p>

<p><sourcexml>url</sourcexml> becomes <targetxml>url</targetxml>.</p>
            <p> <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml> is suppressed, but its content is mapped as follows:</p>
   <p>The content of <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml> is mapped to <targetxml>url/@normval</targetxml>, with the text "http://www." prepended to the value of <targetxml>url/@normval</targetxml>.</p>
<p>The content of <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml> also becomes the content of <targetxml>url</targetxml>. Note that “http://www.” is not prepended to the content of <targetxml>url</targetxml>.</p>
<p> If <sourcexml>emph</sourcexml> occurs as a child <sourcexml>remotelink</sourcexml>, it should be omitted.</p>

<pre>&lt;url&gt;
    &lt;remotelink href="visitscotland.com" hrefclass="http"&gt;
        &lt;emph typestyle="un"&gt;visitscotland.com&lt;/emph&gt;
    &lt;/remotelink&gt;
&lt;/url&gt;

<b>Becomes</b>

&lt;url normval="http://www.visitscotland.com"&gt;visitscotland.com&lt;/url&gt;</pre>
        
